parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sharp Seam on Gas Tank Causing Electrical Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sharp seam on the bottom of the gas tank can cut through the main wiring harness insulation, energizing the tank and creating a potential fire hazard that can lead to catastrophic consequences.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue was discovered during routine maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness insulation can cause electrical shorts, leading to potential fires, engine stalls, or other electrical system malfunctions.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue was discovered during routine maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure - Air in Brake Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the motorcycle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not respond to deceleration attempts
the brakes need to be bled frequently
the brakes work intermittently
the motorcycle does not stop as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or near-misses, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not respond to deceleration attempts
the brakes need to be bled frequently
the brakes work intermittently
the motorcycle does not stop as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective gas cap can cause fuel leaks, leading to fuel smells, vapors, and potentially, fires, especially in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Fuel smell
fuel vapors
gas leaking around the cap
pressure in the tank
gas cap not sealing correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and High Idling Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and high idling issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when attempting to accelerate from a stop. This can also lead to increased fuel consumption and decreased performance.
symptoms: The engine stalls while attempting to accelerate from a stop
the engine idles at high RPM (above 1500)
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to accelerate properly.
